<font color="#FF0000">BROTHERS OF A COMMON BOND</font><br>
<tt>Sat Aug 30 12:43:08 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Cook,<br><br>
I am honored to share such poetry with you.  Only some will know that beyond that thin veneer we call fear lies another realm.  Not a place we discover in an instance, but a place we visit so often we are no longer strangers.  Only Warriors know of this place.  Ed's people know of it well as does he.  It speaks in many tongues, but of one voice.<br><br>
I can feel a tug as I am writing this.  I have brothers that live there now.  We have died and found our way back many times.  Our transition to this realm is only understood by us.  Privileged I think, and cursed for sure.<br><br>
I have heard the sounds of that mistress sucking the last breath from a Warriors lungs over Hanoi one night.  A cruel mistress that waits on those who fear her not.  Time is in her favor. At least she understands she must play on our terms.<br><br>
Brothers
<p><code>--   (Silent Warrior) </code><p>


